The paper focuses on the synthesis of component and connector models, which is a software engineering problem. Therefore, cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses Alloy, a declarative modeling language, to solve the synthesis problem, which suggests that cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also a likely sub-category. The paper involves the use of logic and reasoning, which could fall under cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The paper also mentions the use of architectural styles, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.SY (Systems and Control).
